First, let's find the Cartesian product A × B. This is the set of all ordered pairs (a, b) where a ∈ A and b ∈ B.

A × B = {(1,3), (1,4), (2,3), (2,4)}

Now, let's find the union of (A × B) and C. The union of two sets is the set of all elements that are in either of the two sets.

(A × B) ∪ C = {(1,3), (1,4), (2,3), (2,4)}

So, (A × B) ∪ C = {(1,3), (1,4), (2,3), (2,4)}.
